name: MPMovieAccessLogEvent
desc: A single piece of information for a movie access log.

items.name: var numberOfSegmentsDownloaded: Int
items.desc: A count of media segments downloaded from the web server to your app.

items.name: var playbackStartDate: Date!
items.desc: The timestamp for when playback began for the movie log access event.

items.name: var uri: String!
items.desc: The URI of the playback item.

items.name: var serverAddress: String!
items.desc: The IP address of the web server that was the source of the last delivered media segment. Can be either an IPv4 or an IPv6 address.

items.name: var numberOfServerAddressChanges: Int
items.desc: A count of changes to the serverAddress property over the last uninterrupted period of playback.

items.name: var playbackSessionID: String!
items.desc: A GUID that identifies the playback session. This value is used in HTTP requests.

items.name: var playbackStartOffset: TimeInterval
items.desc: An offset into the playlist where the last uninterrupted period of playback began, in seconds.

items.name: var segmentsDownloadedDuration: TimeInterval
items.desc: The accumulated duration of the media downloaded, in seconds.

items.name: var durationWatched: TimeInterval
items.desc: The accumulated duration of the media played, in seconds.

items.name: var numberOfStalls: Int
items.desc: The total number of playback stalls encountered.

items.name: var numberOfBytesTransferred: Int64
items.desc: The accumulated number of bytes transferred.

items.name: var observedBitrate: Double
items.desc: The empirical throughput across all media downloaded for the movie player, in bits per second.

items.name: var indicatedBitrate: Double
items.desc: The throughput required to play the stream, as advertised by the web server, in bits per second.

items.name: var numberOfDroppedVideoFrames: Int
items.desc: The total number of dropped video frames.
